DiffusionGemma (PR #28054) patch-application step for
container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly.

Adds one COPY+RUN step that applies sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch
(upstream sgl-project/sglang PR #28054, OPEN/unmerged — dLLM Gemma4Renoise
runtime support for google/diffusiongemma-26B-A4B-it) to the sglang Python
source AFTER the SM121 sgl-kernel patches and AFTER the gemma4-nvfp4 patch,
BEFORE `uv pip install ./python`.

Application is gated by build_sm121_image.sh on the recipe variable
APPLY_DIFFUSIONGEMMA_PR28054=1 (set in sglang-0.5.13-gemma4-diffusion-sm121
.recipe; remove / set 0 once PR #28054 is merged into the pinned SGLANG_REF).

NOTE: anchors on the SUCCESS-echo line of the dockerfile-gemma4-nvfp4 block,
so this patch REQUIRES a *gemma4* recipe variant (the gemma4-nvfp4 dockerfile
patch must have been applied first by build_sm121_image.sh). On a non-gemma4
recipe the anchor is absent and the in-container dry-run fails by design.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -296,3 +296,17 @@
     echo 'Gemma-4 NVFP4 patch applied successfully'

+# DiffusionGemma (google/diffusiongemma-26B-A4B-it) runtime support
+# (upstream PR #28054, OPEN/unmerged). Adds the dLLM Gemma4Renoise algorithm,
+# the gemma4_diffusion encoder-decoder model + diffusion_gemma processor, and
+# the modified dLLM/scheduler/server_args touch-points. Applied to the sglang
+# Python source before pip install. Gated by APPLY_DIFFUSIONGEMMA_PR28054=1;
+# anchors AFTER the gemma4-nvfp4 block (requires a *gemma4* recipe variant).
+COPY patches/sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch /tmp/sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    echo "=== Applying sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch (PR #28054) ===" && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch && \
+    test -f python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_diffusion.py && \
+    echo 'DiffusionGemma PR #28054 patch applied successfully'
+
 # Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
